                     <a id="a000283"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-283">
                        <h3 class="content">bluevend</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img alt="bluevend.jpg" src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/bluevend.jpg" width="320" height="240" /></p>

<p><a href="http://www.blinkmedia.org/blinkmedia/blue.htm">bluevend</a> is a project from <a href="http://www.blinkmedia.org/blinkmedia/index.asp">blink</a>. it's a bluetooth vending machine which allows for the distribution of mobile content.  during a brainstorming session at the <a href="http://www.urban-atmospheres.net/Ubicomp2005/">metapolis</a> workshop at ubicomp in 2005, my group was really pushing the idea of a digital content vending machine and it's nice to have come across  people trying to build just that.  of course i think in order for such a system to have an impact it can't be a one-off.  the real interest would rest in their everyday use.</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://www.we-make-money-not-art.com/archives/008175.php">wmmna</a>]</p>
                              
                              <p class="posted">
                                 <span class="post-footers">roxy said on 01:27 AM</span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2006/05/bluevend.html">Permalink</a>
