                        <h3 class="content">khipu: tribal information-as-thing!</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img alt="khipu.jpg" src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/khipu.jpg" width="400" height="200" /></p>

<p><a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2005/050808/full/050808-11.html#B1">nature</a> has a cool article about the inca khipus, which are bunches of knotted colored strings that store numbers.  recently scientists have gotten closer to working out how the numbers are actually stored and finding some clues to what sort of data it might represent.  read on for the full article.</p>

<p><br />
[thanks <a href="http://infosthetics.com/archives/2005/08/khipu.html">information aesthetics</a>]</p>
