                     <h3 class="content">June 07, 2005</h3>
                     <a id="a000178"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-178">
                        <h3 class="content">pulsArt</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img alt="pulsart.jpg" src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/pulsart.jpg" width="400" height="240" /></p>

<p><a href="http://www.tii.se/reform/inthemaking/files/p80.pdf">pulsArt</a> is:<blockquote>a physical and digital installation designed for the home to represent different family members’ level of activity by water running down blocks of salt based on a real-time reading of the individual family member’s pulse.</blockquote>although the prototype is not fully functional, the concept is very interesting.  i really like the marriage of physical, malleable, substances with technology.  i could imagine this being a very beautiful piece, but i wonder if knowing the pulse of say, your blossoming teenage daughter might be a bit tmi... ;]</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://infosthetics.com/archives/2005/06/pulsart_1.html">information aesthetics</a>]</p>
                              
