                     <h3 class="content">May 06, 2005</h3>
                     <a id="a000137"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-137">
                        <h3 class="content">khronos projector</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/khronos1.jpg" width="304" height="152"> <img src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/khronos2.gif" width="202" height="152"></p>

<p>the <a href="http://www.k2.t.u-tokyo.ac.jp/members/alvaro/Khronos/Khronos_Projector.htm">khronos projector</a> is an interactive installation by <a href="http://www.k2.t.u-tokyo.ac.jp/members/alvaro/alvaro-e.html">alvaro cassinelli</a> & <a href="http://www.k2.t.u-tokyo.ac.jp/members/ishikawa/ishikawa-e.html">masatoshi ishikawa</a>. described as:<blockquote>the Khronos Projector is the first Art-Installation enabling the interactive shaping of an arbitrarily complex spatio-temporal cutting surface thanks to a dedicated tangible, "sensual" human-machine interface, and thus giving the user a strong feeling of being actually  sculpting the space-time "substance" with its own hands.</blockquote>check out the videos and stills.  this is a great piece, and it will be at <a href="http://www.siggraph.org/s2005/main.php?f=conference&p=etech&s=etech1&PHPSESSID=f0f7822e647eb6a85558cf8ad5f50207">siggraph 2005</a>.</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://www.we-make-money-not-art.com/archives/005628.php">we make money not art</a>]</p>
                              
