                     <a id="a000126"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-126">
                        <h3 class="content">manual input sessions</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/manual-input-sessions.jpg" width="200" height="150"></p>

<p>golan levin and zachary lieberman, who also did <a href="http://www.tmema.org/messa/messa.html">messa di voce</a>, designed this really pretty <a href="http://tmema.org/mis/">interface/instrument</a>. it uses both standard overhead projecters as well as digital ones producing, as they call it, hybridized dynamic light.  some vision algorithms analyze the shadows of the performer's hands [or various other objects], and then various graphics are projected on top of those shadows.  it is beautiful and playful, although i can't say that i am a huge fan of the music that gets generated. definitely check out the <a href="http://tmema.org/mis/video.html">video</a> to see what i mean.</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://www.we-make-money-not-art.com/archives/005555.php">we make money not art</a>]</p>
                              
                              <p class="posted">
                                 <span class="post-footers">roxy said on 03:11 AM</span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2005/05/manual_input_sessions.html">Permalink</a>
                                 | <a href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2005/05/manual_input_sessions.html#comments">Comments (0)</a>
                                 
                              </p>
                           </div>
                        </div>
